# Self-Review Auto-Fix

When the user runs **self-review**, **audit**, or `/self-review`:

1. Run the [motiful/self-review](https://github.com/motiful/self-review) audit (scope lock → 6 dimensions → artifact verification).
2. **Then auto-fix** all in-scope **Drift** and **Broken** findings — unlike upstream self-review, this project opts into fixes.
3. Re-run `npm run build` and `npm run lint` after fixes; both must pass before calling the work done.
4. Update `README.md` when routes, pages, or persistence behavior changes.
5. Commit with a clear message when the user asked to implement fixes or ship for judges.

## Quality gates (must pass before "done")

- `npm run build` — zero errors
- `npm run lint` — zero errors
- README matches actual `src/pages/` and storage keys
- Demo: chapter data scoped per browser tab session (`fbla:chapter:<sessionId>`)

## Do not auto-fix

- Out-of-scope / deferred items unless the user explicitly expands scope
- Production Firebase/Vercel deploy (document steps; deploy only when credentials are available)
